327
00:18:39,672 --> 00:18:41,192
Every time I went to school with you,

328
00:18:41,791 --> 00:18:43,151
they would say

329
00:18:43,871 --> 00:18:45,672
I was your maid in the An family,

330
00:18:45,871 --> 00:18:47,192
and had a crush on you.

331
00:18:48,391 --> 00:18:49,952
Then why did you never mention it?

332
00:18:52,472 --> 00:18:53,712
Because it was true.

333
00:18:55,032 --> 00:18:56,351
I do like you.

334
00:19:13,831 --> 00:19:15,831
I really want to go back
to high school times.

335
00:19:16,432 --> 00:19:17,551
We leave school together.

336
00:19:18,912 --> 00:19:20,912
Back then, it felt so ordinary.

337
00:19:21,992 --> 00:19:24,032
Too bad we can't go back now.

338
00:19:26,952 --> 00:19:27,752
That's right.

339
00:19:28,831 --> 00:19:29,912
We can't go back.

340
00:19:31,512 --> 00:19:32,672
New Zealand has few people.

341
00:19:32,952 --> 00:19:34,591
It's not easy to gather a group.

342
00:19:38,591 --> 00:19:39,272
Luo Yan,

343
00:19:40,952 --> 00:19:41,672
do you not

344
00:19:41,672 --> 00:19:43,712
want me to go to New Zealand?

345
00:19:47,151 --> 00:19:48,432
This is your life.

346
00:19:48,912 --> 00:19:50,551
What hopes could I have?

347
00:19:57,712 --> 00:19:58,952
I forgot to tell you.

348
00:19:59,472 --> 00:20:01,232
I came here to wait for my brother.

349
00:20:03,311 --> 00:20:03,952
Okay.

350
00:20:03,952 --> 00:20:04,752
I'll leave.

351
